        "content": "<p>This PR proves that a convex function from an open set in a finite dimensional real normed space is locally Lipschitz (in particular continuous) on that set. It depends on four PRs, which are all ready for review:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16111\">feat: <code>a / b * (c / a) = c / b</code> for <code>CommGroupWithZero</code> #16111</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16115\">feat: Local lipschitzness under pointwise operations #16115</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16117\">feat: A function is eventually bounded above/below iff it's eventually <code>BddAbove</code>/<code>BddBelow</code> #16117</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/16118\">feat: A convex function bounded on a set is bounded on its convex hull #16118</a></li>\n</ul>",
